<div class="c-columns">
  <main class="t-landing__main c-columns__content">
    <h1 class="o-heading__level1-getting-started">My Datasets: Getting Started</h1>
    <div class="c-getting-started">
      <h2 class="o-heading__steps">Steps to Share.</h2>
      <ol>
        <li class="c-steps__text-group ">Prepare. Gather your data and the information that others would need to use
          it.(<%= link_to 'Submission Basics', help_path(anchor: 'submission-basics') %>)
        </li>

        <li class="c-steps__text-group ">Describe. Document your dataset. You can choose to describe your dataset a
          little or a lot – including geospatial locations and links to publications and
          datasets.(<%= link_to 'Metadata Basics', help_path(anchor: 'metadata-basics') %>)
        </li>

        <li class="c-steps__text-group ">Upload. Add your dataset through upload form or drag-and-drop. Each file can be
          up to <%= filesize(current_tenant.max_file_size) %>; datasets can be up to
          <%= filesize(current_tenant.max_submission_size) %>
          total.(<%= link_to 'Upload Basics', help_path(anchor: 'upload-basics') %>)
        </li>
      </ol>
      <% if current_user %>
        <%= button_to 'Start New Dataset', new_resource_path, class: 'c-getting-started-heading__button', form_class: 'o-button__inline-form', method: :get %>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </main>

  <aside class="t-landing__sidebar c-columns__sidebar2">
    <div class="c-sidebox">
      <h2 class="c-sidebox__heading">Why Share</h2>
      <div class="">
        <div class="c-why-share__icon"><i class="fa fa-book fa-2x" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="c-why-share__text-group-side">
          <h2 class="o-heading__level2-why-side">Your journal requires it.</h2>
          <div>
            Many publishers &mdash; including PLOS, eLife, and Springer Nature &mdash; require authors to publish the
            data
            underlying papers in a suitable preservation repository.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="c-why-share__icon"><i class="fa fa-bank fa-2x" aria-hidden="true"></i></div>
        <div class="c-why-share__text-group-side">
          <h2 class="o-heading__level2-why-side">Your funder requires it.</h2>
          <div>
            Agencies that fund research &mdash; including all US federal agencies &mdash; are beginning to require
            grantees
            to publish data from funded projects.
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="c-why-share__icon" aria-hidden="true">
          <div aria-hidden="true" class="c-why-share__halo">
            <i class="fa fa-circle-thin fa-2x c-why-share__icon-squish" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </div>
          <div aria-hidden="true" class="c-why-share__user">
            <i class="fa fa-user fa-3x" aria-hidden="true"></i>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="c-why-share__text-group-side">
          <h2 class="o-heading__level2-why-side">It’s the right thing to do.</h2>
          <div>
            By offering clear description of your data including methods and instructions for reuse, you are
            promoting efficiency, transparency, and reproducibility in the research community.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
  </aside>
</div>